      <title>In Besieged Homs, Blood Becomes a Rare Commodity</title>
      <category domain="https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/health/">Health</category>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2017 12:14:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Arwa al-Basha</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/articles/2017/07/25/in-besieged-homs-blood-becomes-a-rare-commodity</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/articles/2017/07/25/in-besieged-homs-blood-becomes-a-rare-commodity</guid>
      <description>At least 32 children in the besieged Houla region are suffering from an inherited blood disorder that requires frequent transfusions. Though fatality rates for thalassemia are not exceptionally high, the absence of supplies and blood banks has made it life-threatening.</description>
